  "explanation": "While embezzlement of $25,000 is a significant breach of trust and requires a penalty to deter future misconduct, there are substantial mitigating factors in this case. The defendant has no prior criminal record, and the fact that partial restitution has already been made shows a willingness to take responsibility and make the victim whole. The spectator's outburst demanding a ten-year sentence is emotional and entirely irrelevant to the legal sentencing guidelines, which I must strictly follow. Balancing the severity of the white-collar offense with the defendant's mitigating circumstances, a brief period of incarceration is appropriate, followed by probation and a mandate for full restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
